  01 Feb 2009; Tobias Klausmann <klausman@gentoo.org>
  hamlib-1.2.8-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on alpha, bug #257055

*hamlib-1.2.8-r1 (27 Dec 2008)

  27 Dec 2008; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> +files/hamlib-ltdl.diff,
  -hamlib-1.2.8.ebuild, +hamlib-1.2.8-r1.ebuild:
  Add patch to allow hamlib to use the system libltdl instead of a bundled
  one, patch by Thomas Beierlein. bug 252326

*hamlib-1.2.8 (04 Dec 2008)

  04 Dec 2008; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> metadata.xml,
  +hamlib-1.2.8.ebuild:
  Version bump, bug #249714:
  New features:
          * Some new rig models supported
          * New rotator backend
          * Fixes for a lot of radios
          * Numerous bindings fixes, esp. for memory channel works
          * New commands available in rigctl
          * New rotctld to go with rigctld rig daemon.
  Added Thomas Beierlein as maintainer, I'll be proxy committer.

  18 Jun 2008; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> -hamlib-1.2.4.ebuild:
  removed old. fixes bug #200597

  18 Jun 2008; Jeremy Olexa <darkside@gentoo.org> hamlib-1.2.6.1.ebuild:
  amd64 stable, proxy commit for gentoofan23. bug #225589

  17 Jun 2008; Christian Faulhammer <opfer@gentoo.org>
  hamlib-1.2.6.1.ebuild:
  stable x86, bug 225589

  15 Jun 2008; Tobias Klausmann <klausman@gentoo.org> hamlib-1.2.4.ebuild:
  No hardware to test, so back to ~alpha for stable version.

*hamlib-1.2.7.1 (10 Jun 2008)

  10 Jun 2008; Samuli Suominen <drac@gentoo.org> -hamlib-1.2.5.ebuild,
  +hamlib-1.2.7.1.ebuild:
  Version bump from Sunrise's portage-review. Remove unnecessary USE flag X
  and gd, since rigmatrix doesn't get built. Thanks to Thomas Beierlein wrt
  #219057.

  09 Nov 2007; Joe Peterson <lavajoe@gentoo.org> hamlib-1.2.6.1.ebuild:
  Add ~x86-fbsd keyword and elibtoolize (bug #198475)

